*numpy is a linear elgebra library for python ,
the reason its so important for data science with python
is that almost all of the library in the pydata ecosystem is
rely on numpy as one of thier main building blocks


*numpy is also incredably fast as it has binding to c libraries

*you can install numpy using 
        conda install numpy 
        pip3 install numpy

* numpy arrays are the main way we will use numpy throughout the course.
* numpy array come in two falvors: vectors and matrices.
* vector are strictly 1-d arrays and matrices ar 2-d (maybe matrix can hold 1 row ro 1 column) 